Actress Chacha Eke Faani, has ended her 9-year-old marriage to Austin Faani. Chacha Eke made the announcement in the wee hours of Tuesday via her Instagram page. The page was only just recently reactivated after news of her mental state broke. According to the mother of four, the need to stay alive rather than leave as a corpse propels her to terminate her marriage noting it’s long been overdue. In October 2020, Eke debunked speculations her marriage crashed over domestic abuse. She claimed she was diagnosed of bipolar disorder; blaming her mental state for the social media outburst.   Erigga asks about ‘Yahoo’ rulers’ penalty over EFCC’s…     Pretty Mike under fire for mocking Christianity     Debate over Tiwa Savage, Tems as Afrobeat queen heats up   Sincerely apologising to the public for misleading them by depicting a blissful life while being married, Chacha for the second time in two years, declared the marriage has ended. Her post title reads: “Leave now alive or leave as a corpse.” She began: “Many have died pretending all is well whilst wishing, hoping and praying for a better tomorrow. I don’t want to “die” or go inexplicably “missing”. I sincerely and publicly apologise for living a lie these past years. True to random speculations, there has been trouble in my ‘perceived paradise’. “For the second time in two years, I am here again on social media boldly declaring that I am done with my marriage. My long overdue/relentless stance on this is of course no news to Austin Faani, the doctors and my parents. She continued: “If push comes to shove & suddenly I am incommunicado; my lawyers, the welfare department and the Nigerian police force have my testimonials in recorded video clips/statements set for public release on all social media apps and national newspapers.” She added: “P.S: old photo”, referring to the post’s photo which capture her hubby and her.